  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  At least 18 years old

          -  Histologically confirmed diagnosis of malignant gliomas that requires systemic
             antineoplastic treatment. Malignant glioma is defined as any of the following:
             Glioblastoma multiforme (GBM); Anaplastic astrocytoma (AA); Anaplastic
             oligodendroglioma; Anaplastic mixed glioma; Glioma not otherwise specified (except
             low-grade glioma)

          -  ECOG performance status score of 0, 1, or 2

          -  Each patient must sign a study-specific informed consent form

        Exclusion Criteria:

        Laboratory values of:

          -  Absolute neutrophil count &lt; 2000/µL

          -  Platelet count &lt; 100,000/µL

          -  AST or ALT &gt; 2 x the upper limit of normal (ULN)

          -  Alkaline phosphatase &gt; 5 x ULN

          -  Bilirubin &gt; 2 x ULN

          -  Creatinine &gt; 2.0 mg/µL

        and

          -  Plan to use any additional cancer therapy (e.g., systemic, radiation, surgery) during
             the study period

          -  Women who are pregnant or lactating
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
